        <section id="system.planet.desc">
            <text id="kerbin">An earhtlike planet with low gravity.</text>
            <text id="mun">Small moon. Sorry, I mean "mun".</text>
            <text id="minmus">Oh, I thought this was a speck on the scanner screen, but it is a teeny tiny moon!</text>
        </section>
        <section id="npc">
            <text id="jeb">Jebediah Kerman</text>
            <text id="valentina">Valentina Kerman</text>
            <text id="bill">Bill Kerman</text>
            <text id="ksc">KSA</text>
        </section>
        <section id="jeb">
            <!-- First contact, no KSC -->
            <text id="contact_no_ksc_1">Hello there! We come in peace, alien lifeform! My name is [color=770000]Jeb[/color]!</text>
            <text id="contact_no_ksc_2">Oh, human you say? What strange skin color!</text>
            <text id="contact_no_ksc_3">You are just in time to witness a historic moment - first [color=550000]Mun[/color] landing by a kerbal! However so far it seems this was only a one-way trip.</text>
            <text id="contact_no_ksc_4">Would you mind helping me out and heading back to that green and blue planet and telling them where I am?</text>
            
            <!-- Before going to KSC -->
            <text id="met_no_ksc">Ne pressure on that rescuing, I got plenty of snacks!</text>
            
            <!-- First contact, talked to KSC -->
            <text id="contact_ksc_1">Hello there! We come in peace, alien lifeform! My name is [color=770000]Jeb[/color]!</text>
            <text id="contact_ksc_2">What do you mean the KSC sent you? I didn't know they outsourced their missions now...</text>
            
            <!-- Waiting for tracker -->
            <text id="tracker_wait">I am curious what plan the KSC will come up with to save me.</text>
            
            <!-- Tracker given -->
            <text id="tracker_done_1">Oh, they gave you a [item=ksc_tracker] for me? Great! With this, [color=770000]Valentina[/color] will have no issue landing right on top of me.</text>
            <text id="tracker_done_2">Well, not literally, I hope.</text>
            
            <!-- Tracker waiting -->
            <text id="tracker_wait">I'm ready whenever you are. Just head to KSC and let them know the [item=ksc_tracker] has been activated.</text>
            
            <!-- Val landed -->
            <text id="val_landed_1">That was such a blast! I never seen anyone pilot a rocket so well, I was barely scorched by the rocket engine!</text>
            
            <!-- Val landed, repeat -->
            <text id="val_landed_no_ksc">When you get to KSC, can you pick me up some snacks? No? Nevermind then.</text>
            
            <!-- Val landed, not completed KSC mission -->
            <text id="val_fuel">When you get all the [item=refined_oil], just hand it to [color=770000]Val[/color], she will know where to put it.</text>
                        
            <!-- After splash down -->
            <text id="good_end_1">Another mission accomplished! Thanks for all the help, I am sure KSC will have some reward for your hard work.</text>
            
            <!-- Returning visits -->
            <text id="return">I got no issue standing here for a while, I got plenty of snacks!</text>
        </section>
        <section id="valentina">
            <!-- Val landed -->
            <text id="val_landed_1">Hello there! Nice to finally meet you. My name is [color=770000]Valentina Kerman[/color], but please call me [color=770000]Val[/color]!</text>
            <text id="val_landed_2">Thanks for helping us with the tracker. I found the right spot easily and landed softly as a feather.</text>
            <text id="val_landed_3">Unfortunately, it seems we did not pack enough fuel for return trip. I guess nobody thought we will manage to land safely, so they wanted to avoid an explosion.</text>
            <text id="val_landed_4">Can you hop over to KSC and let them know what happened?</text>
            
            <!-- Val landed, repeat -->
            <text id="val_landed_no_ksc">Did you have a chance to hop over to KSC and let them know what happened?</text>
            
            <!-- Val landed, not completed KSC mission -->
            <text id="val_fuel">Sorry it's such a lot of [item=refined_oil], our engines are a bit hungry. Let me know when you have it ready!</text>
            
            <!-- Fuel give -->
            <text id="val_fuel_end_1">Wow! You managed to get the [item=refined_oil] so fast?</text>
            <text id="val_fuel_end_2">Let me just pump it into the fuel tanks...</text>
            <text id="val_fuel_end_3">...and we're ready for liftoff! Thanks for everything and see you on [color=550000]Kerbin[/color]!</text>
            
            <!-- After splash down -->
            <text id="good_end_1">Phew! That was quite a ride! Can we do it again?</text>
            
            <!-- Returning visits -->
            <text id="return">I wonder if they'll ever pick us up?</text>
        </section>
        <section id="ksc">
            <!-- First contact, generic -->
            <text id="contact_1">ALERT! ALERT! Unidentified flying object approaching!</text>
            <text id="contact_2">Initite lockdown! Activate red protocol!</text>
            <text id="contact_3">Yes, sir!</text>
            <text id="contact_4">...err, what is the red protocol?</text>
            <text id="contact_5">I though you knew?</text>
            <text id="contact_6">Does anyone know? No? Ok, let me try something else.</text>
            <text id="contact_7">Unidentified flying object, please identify yourself!</text>
            
            <!-- First contact, no Jeb -->
            <text id="contact_no_jeb_1">Another star system you say? But that is impossible!</text>
            <text id="contact_no_jeb_2">But since you're here, can we ask a favor?</text>
            <text id="contact_no_jeb_3">Our first munar mission was a success and we landed a kerbal on the [color=550000]Mun[/color]!</text>
            <text id="contact_no_jeb_4">His name is [color=770000]Jeb[/color] and he is one lucky kerbal! Unfortunately his ship was not so lucky.</text>
            <text id="contact_no_jeb_5">We have prepared a rescue mission, but we need someone to deliver this [item=ksc_tracker] to him.</text>
            <text id="contact_no_jeb_6">Would you help us, please?</text>
            
            <!-- First contact, talked to Jeb -->
            <text id="contact_jeb_1">Another star system you say? But that is impossible!</text>
            <text id="contact_jeb_2">Oh, [color=770000]Jeb[/color] sent you?</text>
            <text id="contact_jeb_3">Then you have heard about our historic success! We landed a kerbal on the [color=550000]Mun[/color]!</text>
            <text id="contact_jeb_4">There is only the minor thing of getting [color=770000]Jeb[/color] back home...</text>
            <text id="contact_jeb_5">We have prepared a rescue mission, but we need someone to deliver this [item=ksc_tracker] to him.</text>
            <text id="contact_jeb_6">Would you help us, please?</text>
            
            <!-- Tracker in progress -->
            <text id="tracker_in_progress">Did you have a chance to deliver the [item=ksc_tracker] to [color=770000]Jeb[/color]? No rush, he is well stocked on snacks, just asking!</text>
            
            <!-- Tracker in progress, not in inventory -->
            <text id="tracker_lost">You lost the [item=ksc_tracker]? Don't worry, we have a warehouse full of them. Here, have another!</text>
            
            <!-- Tracker given, Val launch -->
            <text id="tracker_done_1">So [color=770000]Jeb[/color] has the [item=ksc_tracker]? Great! Now we can launch the rescue mission!</text>
            <text id="tracker_done_2">[color=770000]Valentina[/color], please get ready. Everyone, on your positions! Prepare the launch sequence.</text>
            <text id="tracker_done_3">Open the VAB! Roll out the MEV! Check the OUM levels. Double check delta-V and gamma-R! T-minus 2 hours, we have a lot to do, kerbals!</text>
            <text id="tracker_done_4">Well, that was one great launch.</text>
            <text id="tracker_done_5">Can you please go check if [color=770000]Val[/color] landed okay?</text>
            
            <!-- Val landed -->
            <text id="val_landed_1">That's great news! I meant the ship being intact, not about the fuel, that is rather unfortunate...</text>
            <text id="val_landed_2">Well, seeing you have that great ship and all that, could you maybe help us refuel the ship?</text>
            <text id="val_landed_3">Unfortunately you will also have to find some fuel since we seem to have accidentaly burned it all.</text>
            
            <!-- Val landed, not completed KSC mission -->
            <text id="val_fuel">When you get the [item=refined_oil], just head to [color=550000]Mun[/color] and give it to [color=770000]Val[/color].</text>
            
            <!-- After splash down -->
            <text id="good_end_1">It seems both [color=770000]Jeb[/color] and [color=770000]Val[/color] are safely back on the ground. Thank you so much for this!</text>
            <text id="good_end_2">We hereby declare you a honorary Kerbal for life and as a sign of our appreciation, please accept this ... errr .... this ... [item=ksc_helmet]! Yes, very useful, you'll see!</text>
            
            <!-- Returning visits -->
            <text id="return">Nice to see you again! We are currently preparing a more ambitious mission to [color=550000]Minmus[/color], we'll let you know if we need any help!</text>
        </section>
        <section id="quests">
            <text id="ksc_tracker">Precise Landing</text>
            <text id="ksc_oil">Running On Fumes</text>            
        </section>
        <section id="quest.description">
            <text id="ksc_tracker">needs you to deliver [item=ksc_tracker] to [color=770000]Jeb[/color] so [color=770000]Valentina[/color] can rescue him.</text>
            <text id="ksc_oil">wants you to help refuel [color=770000]Valentina[/color]'s ship so she can bring [color=770000]Jeb[/color] home!</text>
        </section>
        <section id="item.names">
            <text id="ksc_tracker">KSA Tracker</text>
            <text id="ksc_helmet">Kerbal Helmet</text>
        </section>
        <section id="item.descriptions">
            <text id="ksc_tracker">A primitive piece of technology that allows Kerbals to precisely navigate to certain location.</text>
            <text id="ksc_helmet">Seemingly simple helmet which provides unlimited supply of oxygen.</text>
        </section>
